---

Birds flit by in joyous flight,
A symphony of wings unfolds,
In the beauty of flowered targets,
Every tale across the cosmos told.
Through forests thick and rivers wide,
Nature weaves its endless art,
And I, in awe of such divine,
Lose myself and find my heart.

- Rabindranath Tagore
